OL,3,CWhy some soldiers believe their own
OL,4,Cweapons damaged blood vessels in their
OL,5,Cbrain
OL,7,FAVMs are traditionally thought to be
OL,8,Fcongenital, meaning they are genetic
OL,9,Fdisorders present from birth. Only one
OL,10,Fin every hundred thousand people is
OL,11,Fdiagnosed with one in the brain.
OL,13,FHowever, anecdotal evidence suggests
OL,14,Fcases may be far more common among
OL,15,Fsoldiers repeatedly exposed to blast
OL,16,Fshockwaves.
OL,18,FI asked Steven whether he had ever
OL,19,Fconsidered that his own weapons could
OL,20,Fhave caused him harm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
